      • isRepeated

        public static boolean isRepeated(com.google.protobuf.DescriptorProtos.FieldDescriptorProto field)
        Checks the Protobuf field and determines it is repeated field or not.

        Although map fields technically count as repeated, this method will return false for them.

        Parameters:
        field - the descriptor of the field to check
        Returns:
        true if field is repeated, false otherwise

      • isMap

        public static boolean isMap(com.google.protobuf.DescriptorProtos.FieldDescriptorProto field)
        Checks the Protobuf field and determines it is map field or not.

        If a field is a map it is repeated message with the specific type.

        Parameters:
        field - the descriptor of the field to check
        Returns:
        true if field is map, false otherwise

      • getEntryNameFor

        public static java.lang.String getEntryNameFor(com.google.protobuf.DescriptorProtos.FieldDescriptorProto mapField)
        Constructs the entry name for the map field.

        For example, proto field with name 'word_dictionary' has 'wordDictionary' json name. Every map field has corresponding entry type. For 'word_dictionary' it would be 'WordDictionaryEntry'

        Parameters:
        mapField - the field to construct entry name
        Returns:
        the name of the map field

        Returns:

      • trimTypeName

        public static java.lang.String trimTypeName(com.google.protobuf.DescriptorProtos.FieldDescriptorProto fieldDescriptor)
        Removes the leading dot from the Protobuf type name passed as String.

        If there is no leading dots, returns the unmodified parameter.

        Parameters:
        fieldDescriptor - the field descriptor whose type name to modify
        Returns:
        the type name without leading dot
